  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Install the package by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --sysconfdir=/etc \
            --disable-nls \
            --with-ssl=openssl &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <parameter>--with-ssl=openssl</parameter>: This configures the program
        to use OpenSSL instead of GnuTLS which is preferred by the configure
        script.
      </para>

      <para>
        <option>--without-ssl</option>: This configure option is required if
        support for the HTTPS protocol is not needed and OpenSSL is not
        installed.
      </para>

    </sect3>

  </sect2>

